LeConte, 1846b: 206. Type locality: &quot;NovEboraci [= New York]&quot; (original citation). Lectotype (♂), designated by Erwin (1970a: 144), in MCZ [# 5850]. Synonymy established by LeConte (1863a: 524), confirmed by Erwin (1970a: 144).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="476" pageNumber="477">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1868" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Brachinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="476" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptocerus">Brachinus leptocerus</taxonomicName>
